      "description": "Post-Mortem Review for Production Database Outage (INC-2026-0312)\n\nAgenda:\n1. (15 min) Timeline reconstruction — walk through exact sequence of events\n2. (20 min) Root cause analysis — 5 Whys exercise on the BI query issue\n3. (20 min) What went well / what didn't go well\n4. (15 min) Action items and ownership assignment\n5. (20 min) Process improvements — monitoring, alerting, runbooks\n\nRequired Attendees:\n- David Park (DevOps Lead / Incident Commander)\n- Kevin Zhang (DBA Lead) — root cause presenter\n- Sarah Kim (SRE Lead) — monitoring improvements\n- Mike Chen (Backend Lead) — circuit breaker implementation\n\nPre-read:\n- Incident timeline document (Kevin to distribute by EOD Tuesday)\n- Current monitoring dashboard screenshots\n- Connection pool configuration documentation\n\nBlameless Post-Mortem Policy: Focus on systems and processes, not individuals.",
