      },
      "description": "Q1 Infrastructure Planning Review\n\nAgenda:\n1. Database failover improvements — review current RTO/RPO targets\n2. Connection pool tuning — optimal pool size, overflow handling\n3. Monitoring gap analysis — identify blind spots exposed by INC-2026-0312\n4. Q2 capacity planning — projected growth vs current infrastructure\n\nBudget:\n- $45,000 allocated for monitoring tools (Datadog upgrade vs Grafana Cloud)\n- $12,000 for additional read replica provisioning\n- $8,000 for chaos engineering tooling (Gremlin license)\n\nAttendees:\n- David Park (DevOps Lead)\n- Sarah Kim (SRE Lead)\n- Kevin Zhang (DBA Lead)\n- Rachel Adams (VP Engineering) — budget approval authority\n\nDeliverables:\n- Updated infrastructure roadmap for Q2\n- Monitoring tool selection decision\n- Chaos engineering pilot plan",
